# LLM & privacy (BillboardHub)

## Secrets

- No API keys in code or commits. Use `backend/.env`: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `MISTRAL_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET`, etc.
- `IMPORT_USE_LLM=false` forces local heuristics only (no external sample payloads for column mapping).

## Import pipeline

- Prefer `app.services.llm_gateway` (or configured gateway) over ad-hoc client calls scattered in routes.
- Sample rows sent to models should stay minimal (already capped in import flow); never log full `all_rows` or raw client files.

## Tracing (optional)

- If LangSmith/LangChain tracing is enabled, project name and keys come from env — document in `.env.example`, not in code.

## Tools / JSON

- LLM outputs should be strict JSON where used; validate with Pydantic after parse.
